# Content Standards

- Each page must contain exactly one H1.
- Headings must follow logical order: H1 > H2 > H3.
- Link text must clearly describe the destination.
  Never use vague phrases such as "click here" or "read more".
- External links must include target="_blank" and
  rel="noopener noreferrer".
- Empty states must include an explanation and a clear next action.
- Loading states must appear during asynchronous operations.
- Error states must include a human-readable explanation and
  a recovery action.
- Placeholder copy must be replaced before a page is complete.
- 8th grade reading level maximum on all pages.
- Never use: "unhackable", "guaranteed approval",
  "lowest rates in the industry".
